	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=195083><span id= >stacnmae</span></a><br><span id=notbold>7 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Not entirely true with regard to a Bard.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is a situation where Bards would make good use of a shield.  <br><br>If a Bard is relegated to singing AE songs on a raid.  There are 2 primary songs a Bard would use in this case.  AE resists make use of a drum, and AE mana/heal that uses a lute.  With the flooding of the Karana drum on the market almost any raid Bard now has a drum that they can equip in primary.  Now you would think having the epic in secondary is the obvious answer, but in fact it isnt the best option.  The instrument modifier for the mana song increases the amount of healing that is done, but not the amount of mana regen.  During the raid the mana regen is the important thing so the epic isnt really helping any.<br><br>Hence a good shield might give that AE Bard a bit more survivability since those AE songs generate a heap load of agro.  The extra resists help too.  This particular shield is currently the second best Bard usable shield in the game.  Well worth the time if you have access to Plane of Fire.  A good group can take out the nameds that drop the shield.<br><br>Stacatto<br>Terris Thule</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
